Comparatively, the metal-independent FDHs are quite simple enzymes, generally forming homodimers, containing a NAD(H) and a formate-binding pockets in a close vicinity of each other (Fig. 3) [102–109]. The formate-binding site harbours a conserved arginine and asparagine residues, while an aspartate and serine residues make contacts to the nicotinamide ring, with another arginine residue binding the phosphate moiety linker of NAD(H).Fig. 3
